  "learn": {
    "heading": "Multiply, then place the point",
    "intro": "<p>To multiply decimals, first multiply as if there were no decimal points. Then count how many digits are <strong>after the point</strong> in both factors, and put that many after the point in your answer.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>0.3 × 4:</strong> 3 × 4 = 12. One digit after a point (in 0.3), so the answer is <strong>1.2</strong>.",
      "<strong>0.2 × 0.4:</strong> 2 × 4 = 8. Two digits after points total, so the answer is <strong>0.08</strong>."
    ]
